[source](https://doc.rust-lang.org/1.80.0/src/alloc/boxed.rs.html#1759)[Â§](#method.try_from)

Attempts to convert a `Vec<T>` into a `Box<[T; N]>`.

Like [`Vec::into_boxed_slice`](about:blank/vec/struct.Vec.html#method.into_boxed_slice "method std::vec::Vec::into_boxed_slice"), this is in-place if `vec.capacity() == N`, but will require a reallocation otherwise.

##### [Â§](#errors)Errors

Returns the original `Vec<T>` in the `Err` variant if `boxed_slice.len()` does not equal `N`.

##### [Â§](#examples-36)Examples

This can be used with [`vec!`](../macro.vec.html "macro std::vec") to create an array on the heap:

```
let state: Box<[f32; 100]> = vec![1.0; 100].try_into().unwrap();
assert_eq!(state.len(), 100);
```

